0. Setting up common environment

First "source" the "aliases" file by running the following from ledp(Your WS_HOME)

source le-dev/aliases

1. Starting Admin-Console for le-pls EndToEnd tests

First start the le-admin dev console using the following command.

MAVEN_OPTS="-Xdebug -Xnoagent -Djava.compiler=NONE -Xrunjdwp:transport=dt_socket,address=4005,server=y,suspend=n -Xmx1024m -XX:MaxPermSize=256m" mvn -DADMIN_PROPDIR=conf/env/dev -Pfunctional -Djetty.port=8085 -Djavax.net.ssl.trustStore=../le-security/certificates/laca-ldap.dev.lattice.local.jks -Dcom.latticeengines.registerBootstrappers=true jetty:run

Then login to http://localhost:8085/#/tenants/ with the username/password of testuser1/Lattice1

2. Starting PLS server 

Enter "runjettypls"

